A '''flapper valve''' is a type of valve used in flush [[toilet]]s. It creates the watertight seal in the toilet tank that holds the water until flushing. When one pushes the handle, the flapper raises, allowing the water to flush out the excreted items, the flapper then goes back down and recreates the watertight seal.



