Skarv is an [[oil]] and [[gas]] field in the [[Norwegian Sea]] approximately 35 kilometers south-west of the [[Norne oil field]]. It is produced from an FPSO. Remaining reserves are though to be 100 million barrels of oil and 40 billion cubic meters of natural gas.<ref>http://www.npd.no/en/Publications/Facts/Facts-2013/Chapter-10/Skarv/</ref>

The field Skarv was discovered in 1998 and the field started producing 31 December 2012.<ref>[http://www.statoil.com/en/ouroperations/explorationprod/partneroperatedfields/skarv/pages/default.aspx]</ref>

