{{Infobox power station | name = Solarpark Heideblick | name_official = | image = | image_size = frameless{{!}}upright=1.10 | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Germany | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|51|50|N|13|40|E|region:DE_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = Germany | location = [[Heideblick]] | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = September 2, 2011 | decommissioned = | cost = 50 million euros | owner = | operator = | solar_type = PV | ps_units_operational = 115,000 | solar_site_area = {{convert|55|ha|acre|0|abbr=off}} | ps_electrical_capacity = 27.5 [[Megawatt|MW]]<sub>p</sub> | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | ps_annual_generation = 26 [[GWh]] | website = | extra = }}
The '''Solarpark Heideblick''' is a [[photovoltaic power station]] in [[Heideblick]], [[Germany]].<ref>[http://www.pvresources.com/PVPowerPlants/Top50.aspx Large-Scale Photovoltaic Power Plants] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160101115142/http://www.pvresources.com/PVPowerPlants/Top50.aspx |date=2016-01-01 }}</ref> It has a capacity of 27.5&nbsp;[[megawatt]]s (MW). The solar park was developed and built by Enerparc.<ref>[http://www.enerparc.de/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=51:pressemeldung-vom-02092011&catid=10:presse&Itemid=39&lang=en Press Release September 2, 2011]</ref>
The PV project is built on a former military training field, using [[ReneSola]] modules.<ref>[https://archive.is/20120728233115/http://www.enerparc.de/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=29&Itemid=29&lang=en Heideblick, Germany]</ref><ref>[http://www.renewable-energy-sources.com/2011/10/06/renesola-applauds-opening-of-large-scale-german-solar-power-plant-which-utilizes-27-5-mw-of-poly-and-virtus-high-efficiency-modules/ ReneSola Applauds Opening of Large-Scale German Solar Power Plant Which Utilizes 27.5 MW of Poly and Virtus High-Efficiency Modules] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111213113849/http://www.renewable-energy-sources.com/2011/10/06/renesola-applauds-opening-of-large-scale-german-solar-power-plant-which-utilizes-27-5-mw-of-poly-and-virtus-high-efficiency-modules/ |date=2011-12-13 }}</ref>
